Recommendations:
We recommended to the Municipal Mayor to:
Direct the IC to, henceforth, observe the strict compliance to the legal deadline of submission of the RPCPPE as mandated by the MNGAS;
Relieve the members of the Inventory Committee of their regular duties during the inventory taking activities to facilitate immediate completion and timely preparation and submission of the related reports;
Ensure that the IC members familiarize themselves more the provisions of COA Circular No. 2020-006 re: Guidelines in the Conduct of Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (PPE), Recognition of PPE Items Found at Station and Disposition for Non-Existing/Missing PPE Items, for the One-Time Cleansing of PPE Account Balances of Government Agencies to heed the general and specific procedures of the inventory taking activities; and
Closely coordinate with the MACCO during the preliminary and reconciliation stages to accordingly effect the necessary adjustments in the books.

Recommendations:
We recommended to the Municipal Mayor to direct:
The Municipal Accountant and the Acting Municipal Treasurer to reconcile and finalize their records of outstanding checks and the identified stale checks (issued and cancelled);
The Acting Municipal Treasurer to send a written notice to the payee of the existence of the check at least one month before a check becomes stale and issue notices to all the above payees except for those cancelled;
As specified in the foregoing guidelines, the stale checks in the hands of the payee which require replacement may only be issued with a new check upon presentation of the same to the Treasurer with the attached certified copy of the related DV which shall be requested from the COA for presentation to the Administrator/Local Chief Executive who shall countersign the check; and
The Municipal Accountant to record adjusting entries in the books for stale check which replacement has not been processed by the payee despite the serving of written notices to permanently extinguish such a reconciling items.

Recommendations:
We recommended to the Municipal Mayor to:
Ensure that the management preparation of the AIP be enhanced by way of proper planning and specific identification of development projects;
Direct the Municipal Development Council (MDC) to come up with a detailed and specific AIP with consultation and deliberation with the officials concerned;
Specifically require the Punong Barangays to prepare a proposal project before the convening of the MDC and presentation of the same for approval; and
Ensure that identified development projects will actually address environmental management and socio-economic needs of the constituents, as required by the relevant laws, rules and regulations.
